  <Entries>
    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Let's train later, Fatebinder. I need to rest." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>4</ID>
      <DefaultText>"May I offer you the benefit of my wisdom, Fatebinder?" </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>8</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Word of your deeds reaches me, and I enjoy little of what I hear... What do you want with me?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>9</ID>
      <DefaultText>"My Spire is yours, Fatebinder... oh, perhaps I have it backwards. Something about this place makes me just want to... possess it." 

"What can I do for you?" </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>10</ID>
      <DefaultText>A mage purses his lips as he reads one of the many scrolls from your library. He flinches when he notices you. "Ah! Um. Greetings. You must be the keeper of this place."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>11</ID>
      <DefaultText>"When I spotted crates of tomes and scrolls being delivered here, well... my curiosity got the better of me." He laughs uncomfortably.

"I must admit, I wasn't aware that this Spire was occupied. Apologies for the intrusion." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>12</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You can make up for it by training me in the magic of [url=glossary:cairn]Cairn[/url]."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>13</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Lie] "Bad news, friend - you're trapped up here."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>14</ID>
      <DefaultText>His brow rises with interest. "Promise? I have always wanted a student to nurture and perfect over time." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>16</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I... I am? But you seem to come and go by way of that stone pad..." He glances over your shoulder and frowns. 

"Well, this is an inconvenience. I seem to have miscalculated the risks associated with this little venture of mine." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>17</ID>
      <DefaultText>He sighs. "Well, there seem to be food and provisions enough to support a humble mage up here, so with your permission, that is how I shall live out my remaining days atop this drafty, cold Spire."

He glances at the shelves of scrolls with concern. "Hardly an appropriate climate for maintaining vellum, but it will have to do. If you like, we can pass the time by discussing the basics of earth magic?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>18</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Let's talk magic."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>19</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Leave] "I'll make use of your skills later. Farewell."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>20</ID>
      <DefaultText>"May I offer you the benefit of my wisdom, Fatebinder?" </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
  </Entries>
